   homogeneous directions, and fourth-order, compact explicit
   finite-difference schemes in the radial direction). A DNS is carried
   out to simulate for the first time the turbulent Taylor-Couette flow in
   the turbulent regime. Statistical quantities are computed to complement
   the existing experimental information, with a view to compare it to
   planar, pressure-driven turbulent flow at the same value of the
